%N A076427 Number of solutions to Pillai's equation a^x - b^y = n, with a>0, b>0, x>1, y>1.
%C A076427 This is the classic Diophantine equation of S. S. Pillai, who conjectured that there are only a finite number of solutions for each n. A generalization of Catalan's conjecture that a^x-b^y=1 has only one solution. For n <=100, a total of 274 solutions were found for perfect powers less than 10^12. No additional solutions were found for perfect powers < 10^18.
